                <div class="post">
      <h2 class="title">
        <a href="http://www.dinnerwarecenter.com/entertaining/trends-in-home-entertaining-for-2009/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: Trends in Home Entertaining for 2009">Trends in Home Entertaining for 2009</a>
      </h2>
      <p class="date">February 26th 2009 11:18 pm</p>
				<div class="entry">
					<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="size-full wp-image-52 aligncenter piccenter" style="border: black 1px solid;" src="http://entertaining.dinnerwarecenter.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/place-setting.jpg" alt="Lime Green Table Setting" width="346" height="222" title="Trends in Home Entertaining for 2009" /><br />
<strong></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Small Intimate Gatherings:</strong> Goodbye to that guiltÂ to invite one, invite all. Truth is, many couples cannot afford to entertain 40 dinner guests these days. This year will bring smaller dinner parties and a more intimate feel all around.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>More home cooked Food:</strong> Bummer for the caterer, but more hostesses will be preparing their own food this year. The trend so far has been more refined menus prepared with more local grown food (which is almost always cheaper and fresher).<br />
<strong></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Vintage Is In Again:</strong> Hostesses everywhere will be calling up their mothers and grandmothers to borrow those old cake stands and punch bowls. This will not only save money but bring some life back into families&#8217; vintage pieces.<br />
<strong></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>The Good Old Pot Luck:</strong> Eating and Gathering will move back to its more communal roots. No longer will one person feel obligated to provide everything from appetizers to desserts. Friends and family will be more eager to pitch in and make it a group effort.</p>
<h5>How will you change the way you entertain this year? Share your tips!</h5>

